  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a Teku user, I want a readiness probe to answer a yes/no so that I can easily integrate Teku in an orchestration system such as Kubernetes. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nAn endpoint answering:\r\n - 200 if it's fully functional (i.e: not only syncing)\r\n - 503 if the service is not fully functional\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nSee acceptance criteria.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:**\r\nOnly health check exists answering in the OK range 206 partial-content even though it's not fully functional.\r\n\r\n### Versions\r\n* Software version: latest\r\n* Virtual Machine software & version: Kubernetes 1.19.7\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nCurrently, probes implementations require jshell tricks, where they could be nicely integrated using common patterns if this were accepted.",
